==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contignation
<hw>Con`tig*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>contignatio</ets>, fr. <ets>contignare</ets> to join with beams;
<ets>con-</ets> + <ets>tignum</ets> beam.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act or process of framing together, or uniting, as beams in a
fabric.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A framework or fabric, as of beams.</def>
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contiguate</ent>⟦br⟧
